###

### 3.3  Read all Travellers (Admin sees all rows)
GET {{catalog}}/Travellers
Accept: application/json

###

### 3.4  Read Travellers — verify fullName is computed
GET {{catalog}}/Travellers
Accept: application/json
# Verify: fullName = "John Smith" present; not stored in DB

###

### 3.5  Read Traveller with $select including fullName
GET {{catalog}}/Travellers({{travellerId}})
  ?$select=ID,firstName,lastName,fullName,status_code
Accept: application/json

###

### 3.6  Update Traveller — valid PATCH with ETag
PATCH {{catalog}}/Travellers({{travellerId}})
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: {{etag}}

{
  "phone": "+49-151-99999999",
  "status_code": "A"
}

###

### 3.7  EDGE CASE — PATCH without If-Match → 428
PATCH {{catalog}}/Travellers({{travellerId}})
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "+49-151-00000000"
}

###

### 3.8  EDGE CASE — PATCH with stale ETag → 412
PATCH {{catalog}}/Travellers({{travellerId}})
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: W/"stale-etag-value"

{
  "phone": "+49-151-00000000"
}

###

### 3.9  EDGE CASE — CREATE with missing firstName → 400
POST {{catalog}}/Travellers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "christiano",
  "lastName": "OnlyLastName",
  "email": "nofirst@company.com",
  "userID": "nofirst@company.com",
  "type_code": "ST",
  "status_code": "A"
}

###

### 3.10  EDGE CASE — CREATE with duplicate email → 409
POST {{catalog}}/Travellers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Duplicate",
  "email": "john.smith@company.com",
  "userID": "john.smith2@company.com",
  "type_code": "ST",
  "status_code": "A"
}

