### ============================================================
###  SECTION 4 — TRAVELLED LOCATIONS
### ============================================================

### 4.1  Create Location — John in Paris (non-overlapping)
# @name createLoc1
POST {{catalog}}/TravelledLocations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "traveller_ID": "{{travellerId}}",
  "destination_ID": "{{destinationId}}",
  "travelFrom": "2025-03-10",
  "travelTo": "2025-03-17",
  "notes": "Spring conference trip to Paris."
}

###

### 4.2  Create Location — John in Tokyo (different dates, no overlap)
POST {{catalog}}/TravelledLocations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "traveller_ID": "{{travellerId}}",
  "destination_ID": "{{destinationId}}",
  "travelFrom": "2025-05-01",
  "travelTo": "2025-05-08",
  "notes": "Team offsite in Tokyo."
}

###

### 4.3  EDGE CASE — Overlapping dates for same traveller → 409
POST {{catalog}}/TravelledLocations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "traveller_ID": "{{travellerId}}",
  "destination_ID": "{{destinationId}}",
  "travelFrom": "2025-03-14",
  "travelTo": "2025-03-20",
  "notes": "This overlaps the Paris trip — should fail."
}

###

### 4.4  EDGE CASE — travelFrom > travelTo → 400
POST {{catalog}}/TravelledLocations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "traveller_ID": "{{travellerId}}",
  "destination_ID": "{{destinationId}}",
  "travelFrom": "2025-06-15",
  "travelTo": "2025-06-10",
  "notes": "Invalid: start is after end."
}

###

### 4.5  Read all Locations for current user
GET {{catalog}}/TravelledLocations
Accept: application/json

###

### 4.6  Delete a Location
DELETE {{catalog}}/TravelledLocations({{locationId}})

###

### 4.7  EDGE CASE — PATCH Location is not allowed → 405
PATCH {{catalog}}/TravelledLocations({{locationId}})
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "notes": "Trying to update immutable record."
}

###


