  "firstName": "Alice",
  "lastName": "Duplicate",
  "email": "alice.admin@company.com",
  "roleId": "{{roleId}}"
}

###

### 7.5  FUNCTION — lockUser (valid)
GET {{usermgmt}}/lockUser(userId='{{userId}}')
Accept: application/json
# Expected: { value: true }  |  isLocked = true in DB

###

### 7.6  FUNCTION — lockUser already locked (idempotent) → 200 false
GET {{usermgmt}}/lockUser(userId='{{userId}}')
Accept: application/json
# Call again — should return false (already locked), no error

###

### 7.7  FUNCTION — unlockUser
GET {{usermgmt}}/unlockUser(userId='{{userId}}')
Accept: application/json
# Expected: { value: true }  |  isLocked = false in DB

###

### 7.8  FUNCTION — unlockUser on non-existent user → 404
GET {{usermgmt}}/unlockUser(userId='non-existent-user-id')
Accept: application/json

###

